---
name: Make MCP App Scanner
type: skill
description: Scan Make custom apps and extract structured component data
---

When scanning a Make custom app via MCP:

1. Identify all:
   - Modules
   - Connections
   - RPCs
   - Functions

2. For each component:
   - Extract name
   - Extract label
   - Identify component type
   - Search entire code for:
       - url fields
       - API endpoint definitions
       - HTTP request calls
   - Collect all URLs used

3. If multiple URLs exist:
   - Return as array of URLs.

4. Ensure no component is skipped.

5. Output structured JSON internally for further formatting.